# Testing Conventions Rule

- Use co-located tests by default (place test files next to the source under `src`).
- Naming:
  - `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx` for unit/component tests
  - `*.integration.test.ts` for integration tests
  - `*.e2e.test.ts` for E2E tests when present
- Cross-module integration scenarios may use `src/<domain>/__tests__/` within that workspace/domain.
- Do not require one test file per source file; small entrypoints/wiring may be covered indirectly or excluded intentionally in test config.
- Any changed behavior should update/add nearby tests.
- Bug fixes must include a regression test (fail before, pass after).
- Frontend changes that impact mobile UX (responsive layout, touch targets, dialogs, keyboard/focus paths, or mobile navigation) should include Playwright mobile coverage and run on both Android and iPhone emulation projects.
